column5: Me and the family (5)will be there .  The boys and I for 7 am ( gotta get the coffee there on time ) and the Mrs and daughter mid morning ( they bring the hot choc !)  Due to the excellent conditions me and the boys plan on walking out for a shot at some bigger fish  Moving back in when the girls show up and get the hut and heat set up .  TB
Touche my friend...touche...LOL.
See you guys tomorrow!  Tony
I will be there with my other half and son. See you all there.
I will be there, bringing a buddy  G
Me and my little one will be there,  Was going to fish near Tbayboy but now I am not too sure  Would not miss this event

I'm picking up the sausssages this morning and Beans and I will be out of here about 5:00 am tomorrow, should be there by 7ish to help with whatever.  Beans, do not try to come down the driveway, it is all ice, I have put sand down but there are still slippery spots. I will be at the garage with the truck warmed up at 5:00 am so if you are here a few minutes early just park in front of the garage and wait. I don't want you falling or anything.
I'll try to be there.

I don't want me falling either...  I was going to call you to find out where to park...thanks  Prob hit the hay after supper tonight...Got the alarm set for Lew o'clock...(03:00 AM...)...should give me lots of time to take care of the zoo...check the board...etc.  Getting anxious...see ya at 05:00 AM
Been catching them good in the area so see you there.
Sorry, I can't make it.  But will send out a donation as my replacement!  Goodluck on the ice everyone  reefrunner

Ken ( Bowshep) myself and our friend Peter will be there...  I have the prizes that AL FLAHERTY'S Donated and will bring them  also I know Ryan ( hammerhead Lures) will be there and I think his cousin....   MO  if you need anything call me (647) 832-0994   dave
From what I've heard, yes, just enough snow to lub the sliders.
Wish I could make it....goood luck everyone and have fun and take lots of pictures!

I know many of you are coming on Saturday, and I look forward to seeing those I know and meeting those I don't  Just wondering how many I might expect to see, looks like it's going to be a bright sunny day, so douG if you're going to make it, don't forget the sunscreen this year  Maureen
Bly and I will be there with Fishnsled!

looks like I will be dragging my butt out there

Ill be there!! First time out on the Ice... No hut but ill be there anyways I hope somone will let me warm up once and awhile or im gonna feel like a popsicle by 10:00 Am LOL Anyways See you all there.....BMM   Yahoo Thanks Bill Parker now i got a place to warm up and some company too !!

Doh, I can't believe I did that - your right I'm cursed now.  Ahh well plan B - fish anywhere away from Cliff and his ice fishing tack record hehe  Stoty - we're talking about the Fishing for Tyler even in Innisfil this Saturday
I will be there along with 2 or 3 others.

I'll be there, but I regretably won't make it for the derby - I am helping my fishing partner move his hut from Gilford up to Innissfil. My hut is the big blue one ( black roof ) straight out from the boat launch, anyone needing to get out of the wind and warm up - doors unlocked. I should be up there around noon. This is a picture of the hut:   Please go in and warm up.    Don   It is off to the left in 80 fow

Mo... Very sorry to say that 'LilBrick an myself will not be comming afterall... It has been in the plans since last years and even marked in my daily diary. I am hosting one of my brothers 50th B-Day g2g'rs and had planned to bring everyone to Tyler's g2g for a great day on the ice for an even better cause BUT..... The majority ruled me out giving the BOQ the nod. Their reasoning was,  "They didnt want to be around young folk and families". I can only surmise it is so they can go 'HogWild'... I'm now (asof this past Tuesday) not bringing 'LilBrick either....she's P.O'd. Well THEY....are not avid fisherman either....... I'll have to lay the law down a litle out there and keep them in line.  Mo....I've your address from the year before..... If it's the same I'lll send my event donation regardless. If not the same address.PM me...K. Best of luck for a record raising amount for this great cause.
